  "text": "There have been doubts about the prognostic value of SPECT in certain subgroups. Studies have shown that women [CITATION_1] , patients with renal impairment (eGFR<60) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and patients with atrial fibrillation (AF) [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] have a higher event rate after normal SPECT. Furthermore, the prognostic use of SPECT in diabetic patients and patients with left bundle branch block (LBBB) has also been disputed.",
